  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2010-05-11",
    "date": "2010-06-30T21:06:05Z",
    "text": "National Disaster Tax Extenders Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude a casualty loss tax deduction for disaster losses sustained after December 31, 2009, and before January 1, 2011, from an individual's gross income in determining adjusted gross income. Extends through 2010: (1) such casualty loss deduction; (2) expensing of disaster abatement and cleanup expenses; (3) the five-year carryback period of net operating losses attributable to federally declared disasters; and (4) the special depreciation allowance for qualified disaster assistance property."
  },
